# Bat_OS .gitignore

# Cargo build artifacts — reproducible via `cargo build`.
/target

# STUMP #136 (Phase 7): persistent BatFS disk image and any other
# host-side state files Bat_OS needs across QEMU invocations. The
# image is auto-created on first boot — wipe with `rm state/batfs.img`
# to start fresh. Never commit user data.
/state

.DS_Store

# Compressed logs from past sessions (regenerable).
*.log

# Claude Code / harness local state (not project state).
/.claude
/.claude-flow
/.mcp.json
# Harness state also shows up inside vendored submodules.
**/.claude-flow/
**/__pycache__/

# Bring-up research data: macos_dump/ stays tracked (split into .partNN
# chunks; see macos_dump/README.md for reassembly).
#
# captures/ went the other way: re-untracked on 2026-05-08 after the
# case-insensitive APFS bug was diagnosed. The original 5-batch commit
# series (A-Z + lowercase) created blob-level duplicates that show up as
# 2,930 phantom modifications because uppercase G001.png and lowercase
# g001.png resolve to the same on-disk file. The historical captures
# stay in git history (recoverable via tag pre-no-browser-2026-05-07);
# new captures live local-only.
/captures

# Split-file parts — don't track source files if they're already split.
macos_dump/kernelcache.mac16j.bin
macos_dump/SystemKernelExtensions.kc

# Autopilot harness state (the autopilot infrastructure survives the
# no-browser pivot but no longer drives Ladybird; reusable for other
# STUMP loops).
.autopilot-session-id
.autopilot-session-started
